    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-12T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.933/244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-13T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 13, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 13—6
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the Legation’s telegram January 8, 10 a.m.,<note n="49"
                        xml:id="d442fn49">Copy apparently not received in the Department; see
                        Department’s telegram No. 6, January 6, to the Chargé in China, <ref
                            target="#pg_360">p. 360</ref>.</note> I visited informally Mayor of
                    Canton on January 11 when I took occasion to assure him of cooperation of
                    American Consulate General and discussed several pending matters. Mayor has
                    arranged to return visit today. Other Consuls are pursuing similar course, and
                    relations now seem well established. Department and Legation informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
